A bell rings every 25 minutes while another bell rings every 40 minutes.  If the bells rang together at 6 A.M., at what time would they next ring together?

}

\textbf{Answer:} The lowest common multiple of 25 and 40 is 200.  200 minutes is 3 hours and 20 minutes, which means the bells will ring together at $\boxed{9:20}$ A.M.
